LocalBusiness.title: LocalBusiness
LocalBusiness.description: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.

Dataset.title: Dataset
Dataset.description: A body of structured information describing some topic(s) of interest.

LodgingBusiness.title: LodgingBusiness
LodgingBusiness.description: A lodging business, such as a motel, hotel, or inn.

Thesis.title: Thesis
Thesis.description: A thesis or dissertation document submitted in support of candidature for an academic degree or professional qualification.

ProductModel.title: ProductModel
ProductModel.description: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).

MovieSeries.title: MovieSeries
MovieSeries.description: A series of movies. Included movies can be indicated with the hasPart property.

PublicToilet.title: PublicToilet
PublicToilet.description: A public toilet is a room or small building containing one or more toilets (and possibly also urinals) which is available for use by the general public, or by customers or employees of certain businesses.

Airline.title: Airline
Airline.description: An organization that provides flights for passengers.

MiddleSchool.title: MiddleSchool
MiddleSchool.description: A middle school (typically for children aged around 11-14, although this varies somewhat).

RadioChannel.title: RadioChannel
RadioChannel.description: A unique instance of a radio BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

Nerve.title: Nerve
Nerve.description: A common pathway for the electrochemical nerve impulses that are transmitted along each of the axons.

BroadcastService.title: BroadcastService
BroadcastService.description: A delivery service through which content is provided via broadcast over the air or online.

LiquorStore.title: LiquorStore
LiquorStore.description: A shop that sells alcoholic drinks such as wine, beer, whisky and other spirits.

Optician.title: Optician
Optician.description: A store that sells reading glasses and similar devices for improving vision.

Thing.title: Thing
Thing.description: The most generic type of item.

MediaObject.title: MediaObject
MediaObject.description: A media object, such as an image, video, or audio object embedded in a web page or a downloadable dataset i.e. DataDownload. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).

PhysicalExam.title: PhysicalExam
PhysicalExam.description: A type of physical examination of a patient performed by a physician.

SocialMediaPosting.title: SocialMediaPosting
SocialMediaPosting.description: A post to a social media platform, including blog posts, tweets, Facebook posts, etc.

PawnShop.title: PawnShop
PawnShop.description: A shop that will buy, or lend money against the security of, personal possessions.

MedicalTherapy.title: MedicalTherapy
MedicalTherapy.description: Any medical intervention designed to prevent, treat, and cure human diseases and medical conditions, including both curative and palliative therapies. Medical therapies are typically processes of care relying upon pharmacotherapy, behavioral therapy, supportive therapy (with fluid or nutrition for example), or detoxification (e.g. hemodialysis) aimed at improving or preventing a health condition.

PodcastSeries.title: PodcastSeries
PodcastSeries.description: A podcast is an episodic series of digital audio or video files which a user can download and listen to.

WebPage.title: WebPage
WebPage.description: A web page. Every web page is implicitly assumed to be declared to be of type WebPage, so the various properties about that webpage, such as breadcrumb may be used. We recommend explicit declaration if these properties are specified, but if they are found outside of an itemscope, they will be assumed to be about the page.

Muscle.title: Muscle
Muscle.description: A muscle is an anatomical structure consisting of a contractile form of tissue that animals use to effect movement.

Place.title: Place
Place.description: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

BioChemEntity.title: BioChemEntity
BioChemEntity.description: Any biological, chemical, or biochemical thing. For example: a protein; a gene; a chemical; a synthetic chemical.

SurgicalProcedure.title: SurgicalProcedure
SurgicalProcedure.description: A medical procedure involving an incision with instruments; performed for diagnose, or therapeutic purposes.

PerformingGroup.title: PerformingGroup
PerformingGroup.description: A performance group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a circus.

MusicPlaylist.title: MusicPlaylist
MusicPlaylist.description: A collection of music tracks in playlist form.

SheetMusic.title: SheetMusic
SheetMusic.description: Printed music, as opposed to performed or recorded music.

SeaBodyOfWater.title: SeaBodyOfWater
SeaBodyOfWater.description: A sea (for example, the Caspian sea).

VisualArtwork.title: VisualArtwork
VisualArtwork.description: A work of art that is primarily visual in character.

Play.title: Play
Play.description: A play is a form of literature, usually consisting of dialogue between characters, intended for theatrical performance rather than just reading. Note the peformance of a Play would be a TheaterEvent - the Play being the workPerformed.

BusOrCoach.title: BusOrCoach
BusOrCoach.description: A bus (also omnibus or autobus) is a road vehicle designed to carry passengers. Coaches are luxury busses, usually in service for long distance travel.

ComputerLanguage.title: ComputerLanguage
ComputerLanguage.description: This type covers computer programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, as well as other language-like computer representations. Natural languages are best represented with the Language type.

State.title: State
State.description: A state or province of a country.

TVSeries.title: TVSeries
TVSeries.description: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to TV broadcast and associated online delivery.

Continent.title: Continent
Continent.description: One of the continents (for example, Europe or Africa).

Resort.title: Resort
Resort.description:
A resort is a place used for relaxation or recreation, attracting visitors for holidays or vacations. Resorts are places, towns or sometimes commercial establishment operated by a single company (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resort).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

AdministrativeArea.title: AdministrativeArea
AdministrativeArea.description: A geographical region, typically under the jurisdiction of a particular government.

VideoGame.title: VideoGame
VideoGame.description: A video game is an electronic game that involves human interaction with a user interface to generate visual feedback on a video device.

BroadcastChannel.title: BroadcastChannel
BroadcastChannel.description: A unique instance of a BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

Course.title: Course
Course.description: A description of an educational course which may be offered as distinct instances at which take place at different times or take place at different locations, or be offered through different media or modes of study. An educational course is a sequence of one or more educational events and/or creative works which aims to build knowledge, competence or ability of learners.

CreativeWork.title: CreativeWork
CreativeWork.description: The most generic kind of creative work, including books, movies, photographs, software programs, etc.

DrugLegalStatus.title: DrugLegalStatus
DrugLegalStatus.description: The legal availability status of a medical drug.

RadiationTherapy.title: RadiationTherapy
RadiationTherapy.description: A process of care using radiation aimed at improving a health condition.

Substance.title: Substance
Substance.description: Any matter of defined composition that has discrete existence, whose origin may be biological, mineral or chemical.

DefenceEstablishment.title: DefenceEstablishment
DefenceEstablishment.description: A defence establishment, such as an army or navy base.

RadioSeries.title: RadioSeries
RadioSeries.description: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

MusicRelease.title: MusicRelease
MusicRelease.description: A MusicRelease is a specific release of a music album.

Bone.title: Bone
Bone.description: Rigid connective tissue that comprises up the skeletal structure of the human body.

Chapter.title: Chapter
Chapter.description: One of the sections into which a book is divided. A chapter usually has a section number or a name.

MedicalSymptom.title: MedicalSymptom
MedicalSymptom.description: Any complaint sensed and expressed by the patient (therefore defined as subjective)  like stomachache, lower-back pain, or fatigue.

MedicalSign.title: MedicalSign
MedicalSign.description: Any physical manifestation of a person's medical condition discoverable by objective diagnostic tests or physical examination.

TheaterGroup.title: TheaterGroup
TheaterGroup.description: A theater group or company, for example, the Royal Shakespeare Company or Druid Theatre.

PlaceOfWorship.title: PlaceOfWorship
PlaceOfWorship.description: Place of worship, such as a church, synagogue, or mosque.

Occupation.title: Occupation
Occupation.description: A profession, may involve prolonged training and/or a formal qualification.

Canal.title: Canal
Canal.description: A canal, like the Panama Canal.

Drawing.title: Drawing
Drawing.description: A picture or diagram made with a pencil, pen, or crayon rather than paint.

EmergencyService.title: EmergencyService
EmergencyService.description: An emergency service, such as a fire station or ER.

QuantitativeValue.title: QuantitativeValue
QuantitativeValue.description: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.

RiverBodyOfWater.title: RiverBodyOfWater
RiverBodyOfWater.description: A river (for example, the broad majestic Shannon).

Car.title: Car
Car.description: A car is a wheeled, self-powered motor vehicle used for transportation.

Collection.title: Collection
Collection.description: A created collection of Creative Works or other artefacts.

MedicalOrganization.title: MedicalOrganization
MedicalOrganization.description: A medical organization (physical or not), such as hospital, institution or clinic.

Newspaper.title: Newspaper
Newspaper.description: A publication containing information about varied topics that are pertinent to general information, a geographic area, or a specific subject matter (i.e. business, culture, education). Often published daily.

AnatomicalStructure.title: AnatomicalStructure
AnatomicalStructure.description: Any part of the human body, typically a component of an anatomical system. Organs, tissues, and cells are all anatomical structures.

Episode.title: Episode
Episode.description: A media episode (e.g. TV, radio, video game) which can be part of a series or season.

SportsActivityLocation.title: SportsActivityLocation
SportsActivityLocation.description: A sports location, such as a playing field.

MedicalSpecialty.title: MedicalSpecialty
MedicalSpecialty.description: Any specific branch of medical science or practice. Medical specialities include clinical specialties that pertain to particular organ systems and their respective disease states, as well as allied health specialties. Enumerated type.

MobileApplication.title: MobileApplication
MobileApplication.description: A software application designed specifically to work well on a mobile device such as a telephone.

Ligament.title: Ligament
Ligament.description: A short band of tough, flexible, fibrous connective tissue that functions to connect multiple bones, cartilages, and structurally support joints.

BodyOfWater.title: BodyOfWater
BodyOfWater.description: A body of water, such as a sea, ocean, or lake.

ComicSeries.title: ComicSeries
ComicSeries.description:
A sequential publication of comic stories under a
    unifying title, for example "The Amazing Spider-Man" or "Groo the
    Wanderer".

ComicStory.title: ComicStory
ComicStory.description:
The term "story" is any indivisible, re-printable
    unit of a comic, including the interior stories, covers, and backmatter. Most
    comics have at least two stories: a cover (ComicCoverArt) and an interior story.

Vehicle.title: Vehicle
Vehicle.description: A vehicle is a device that is designed or used to transport people or cargo over land, water, air, or through space.

EventSeries.title: EventSeries
EventSeries.description:
A series of Events. Included events can relate with the series using the superEvent property.

An EventSeries is a collection of events that share some unifying characteristic. For example, "The Olympic Games" is a series, which is repeated regularly. The "2012 London Olympics" can be presented both as an Event in the series "Olympic Games", and as an EventSeries that included a number of sporting competitions as Events.

The nature of the association between the events in an EventSeries can vary, but typical examples could include a thematic event series (e.g. topical meetups or classes), or a series of regular events that share a location, attendee group and/or organizers.

EventSeries has been defined as a kind of Event to make it easy for publishers to use it in an Event context without worrying about which kinds of series are really event-like enough to call an Event. In general an EventSeries may seem more Event-like when the period of time is compact and when aspects such as location are fixed, but it may also sometimes prove useful to describe a longer-term series as an Event.

CivicStructure.title: CivicStructure
CivicStructure.description: A public structure, such as a town hall or concert hall.

ArchiveOrganization.title: ArchiveOrganization
ArchiveOrganization.description: An organization with archival holdings. An organization which keeps and preserves archival material and typically makes it accessible to the public.

MedicalEntity.title: MedicalEntity
MedicalEntity.description: The most generic type of entity related to health and the practice of medicine.

InfectiousDisease.title: InfectiousDisease
InfectiousDisease.description: An infectious disease is a clinically evident human disease resulting from the presence of pathogenic microbial agents, like pathogenic viruses, pathogenic bacteria, fungi, protozoa, multicellular parasites, and prions. To be considered an infectious disease, such pathogens are known to be able to cause this disease.

Protein.title: Protein
Protein.description: Protein is here used in its widest possible definition, as classes of amino acid based molecules. Amyloid-beta Protein in human (UniProt P05067), eukaryota (e.g. an OrthoDB group) or even a single molecule that one can point to are all of type schema:Protein. A protein can thus be a subclass of another protein, e.g. schema:Protein as a UniProt record can have multiple isoforms inside it which would also be schema:Protein. They can be imagined, synthetic, hypothetical or naturally occurring.

Report.title: Report
Report.description: A Report generated by governmental or non-governmental organization.

WebSite.title: WebSite
WebSite.description: A WebSite is a set of related web pages and other items typically served from a single web domain and accessible via URLs.

Hostel.title: Hostel
Hostel.description:
A hostel - cheap accommodation, often in shared dormitories.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

Reservoir.title: Reservoir
Reservoir.description: A reservoir of water, typically an artificially created lake, like the Lake Kariba reservoir.

Language.title: Language
Language.description: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. Formal language code tags expressed in BCP 47 can be used via the alternateName property. The Language type previously also covered programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, which are now best represented using ComputerLanguage.

MolecularEntity.title: MolecularEntity
MolecularEntity.description: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

Campground.title: Campground
Campground.description:
A camping site, campsite, or Campground is a place used for overnight stay in the outdoors, typically containing individual CampingPitch locations.

In British English a campsite is an area, usually divided into a number of pitches, where people can camp overnight using tents or camper vans or caravans; this British English use of the word is synonymous with the American English expression campground. In American English the term campsite generally means an area where an individual, family, group, or military unit can pitch a tent or park a camper; a campground may contain many campsites (Source: Wikipedia see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Campsite).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

Motel.title: Motel
Motel.description:
A motel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

DanceGroup.title: DanceGroup
DanceGroup.description: A dance group—for example, the Alvin Ailey Dance Theater or Riverdance.

CreativeWorkSeries.title: CreativeWorkSeries
CreativeWorkSeries.description:
A CreativeWorkSeries in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. CreativeWorkSeries are usually organized into some order, often chronological. Unlike ItemList which is a general purpose data structure for lists of things, the emphasis with CreativeWorkSeries is on published materials (written e.g. books and periodicals, or media such as tv, radio and games).

Specific subtypes are available for describing TVSeries, RadioSeries, MovieSeries, BookSeries, Periodical and VideoGameSeries. In each case, the hasPart / isPartOf properties can be used to relate the CreativeWorkSeries to its parts. The general CreativeWorkSeries type serves largely just to organize these more specific and practical subtypes.

It is common for properties applicable to an item from the series to be usefully applied to the containing group. Schema.org attempts to anticipate some of these cases, but publishers should be free to apply properties of the series parts to the series as a whole wherever they seem appropriate.

WorkersUnion.title: WorkersUnion
WorkersUnion.description: A Workers Union (also known as a Labor Union, Labour Union, or Trade Union) is an organization that promotes the interests of its worker members by collectively bargaining with management, organizing, and political lobbying.

Landform.title: Landform
Landform.description: A landform or physical feature.  Landform elements include mountains, plains, lakes, rivers, seascape and oceanic waterbody interface features such as bays, peninsulas, seas and so forth, including sub-aqueous terrain features such as submersed mountain ranges, volcanoes, and the great ocean basins.

Apartment.title: Apartment
Apartment.description: An apartment (in American English) or flat (in British English) is a self-contained housing unit (a type of residential real estate) that occupies only part of a building (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apartment).

MusicGroup.title: MusicGroup
MusicGroup.description: A musical group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a choir. Can also be a solo musician.

Motorcycle.title: Motorcycle
Motorcycle.description: A motorcycle or motorbike is a single-track, two-wheeled motor vehicle.

TherapeuticProcedure.title: TherapeuticProcedure
TherapeuticProcedure.description: A medical procedure intended primarily for therapeutic purposes, aimed at improving a health condition.

MedicalProcedure.title: MedicalProcedure
MedicalProcedure.description: A process of care used in either a diagnostic, therapeutic, preventive or palliative capacity that relies on invasive (surgical), non-invasive, or other techniques.

MedicalTest.title: MedicalTest
MedicalTest.description: Any medical test, typically performed for diagnostic purposes.

MedicalSignOrSymptom.title: MedicalSignOrSymptom
MedicalSignOrSymptom.description: Any feature associated or not with a medical condition. In medicine a symptom is generally subjective while a sign is objective.

PublicationVolume.title: PublicationVolume
PublicationVolume.description:
A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or multi-volume work, often numbered. It may represent a time span, such as a year.

See also blog post.

NewsArticle.title: NewsArticle
NewsArticle.description:
A NewsArticle is an article whose content reports news, or provides background context and supporting materials for understanding the news.

A more detailed overview of schema.org News markup is also available.

Article.title: Article
Article.description:
An article, such as a news article or piece of investigative report. Newspapers and magazines have articles of many different types and this is intended to cover them all.

See also blog post.

GeoCoordinates.title: GeoCoordinates
GeoCoordinates.description: The geographic coordinates of a place or event.

MedicalGuideline.title: MedicalGuideline
MedicalGuideline.description: Any recommendation made by a standard society (e.g. ACC/AHA) or consensus statement that denotes how to diagnose and treat a particular condition. Note: this type should be used to tag the actual guideline recommendation; if the guideline recommendation occurs in a larger scholarly article, use MedicalScholarlyArticle to tag the overall article, not this type. Note also: the organization making the recommendation should be captured in the recognizingAuthority base property of MedicalEntity.

TouristAttraction.title: TouristAttraction
TouristAttraction.description: A tourist attraction. In principle any Thing can be a TouristAttraction, from a Mountain and LandmarksOrHistoricalBuildings to a LocalBusiness. This Type can be used on its own to describe a general TouristAttraction, or be used as an additionalType to add tourist attraction properties to any other type. (See examples below)

Manuscript.title: Manuscript
Manuscript.description: A book, document, or piece of music written by hand rather than typed or printed.

FinancialProduct.title: FinancialProduct
FinancialProduct.description: A product provided to consumers and businesses by financial institutions such as banks, insurance companies, brokerage firms, consumer finance companies, and investment companies which comprise the financial services industry.

PublicationIssue.title: PublicationIssue
PublicationIssue.description:
A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or publication volume, often numbered, usually containing a grouping of works such as articles.

See also blog post.

TVSeason.title: TVSeason
TVSeason.description: Season dedicated to TV broadcast and associated online delivery.

Artery.title: Artery
Artery.description: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries blood away from the heart.

Hotel.title: Hotel
Hotel.description:
A hotel is an establishment that provides lodging paid on a short-term basis (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

TelevisionChannel.title: TelevisionChannel
TelevisionChannel.description: A unique instance of a television BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

Brand.title: Brand
Brand.description: A brand is a name used by an organization or business person for labeling a product, product group, or similar.

Event.title: Event
Event.description: An event happening at a certain time and location, such as a concert, lecture, or festival. Ticketing information may be added via the offers property. Repeated events may be structured as separate Event objects.

Periodical.title: Periodical
Periodical.description:
A publication in any medium issued in successive parts bearing numerical or chronological designations and intended, such as a magazine, scholarly journal, or newspaper to continue indefinitely.

See also blog post.

BookSeries.title: BookSeries
BookSeries.description: A series of books. Included books can be indicated with the hasPart property.

MedicalClinic.title: MedicalClinic
MedicalClinic.description: A facility, often associated with a hospital or medical school, that is devoted to the specific diagnosis and/or healthcare. Previously limited to outpatients but with evolution it may be open to inpatients as well.

CollegeOrUniversity.title: CollegeOrUniversity
CollegeOrUniversity.description: A college, university, or other third-level educational institution.

SportsOrganization.title: SportsOrganization
SportsOrganization.description: Represents the collection of all sports organizations, including sports teams, governing bodies, and sports associations.

TVEpisode.title: TVEpisode
TVEpisode.description: A TV episode which can be part of a series or season.

Atlas.title: Atlas
Atlas.description: A collection or bound volume of maps, charts, plates or tables, physical or in media form illustrating any subject.

Legislation.title: Legislation
Legislation.description: A legal document such as an act, decree, bill, etc. (enforceable or not) or a component of a legal act (like an article).

BloodTest.title: BloodTest
BloodTest.description: A medical test performed on a sample of a patient's blood.

ParkingFacility.title: ParkingFacility
ParkingFacility.description: A parking lot or other parking facility.

Rating.title: Rating
Rating.description: A rating is an evaluation on a numeric scale, such as 1 to 5 stars.

GovernmentOffice.title: GovernmentOffice
GovernmentOffice.description: A government office—for example, an IRS or DMV office.

CreativeWorkSeason.title: CreativeWorkSeason
CreativeWorkSeason.description: A media season e.g. tv, radio, video game etc.

PerformingArtsTheater.title: PerformingArtsTheater
PerformingArtsTheater.description: A theater or other performing art center.

Organization.title: Organization
Organization.description: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

MedicalCondition.title: MedicalCondition
MedicalCondition.description: Any condition of the human body that affects the normal functioning of a person, whether physically or mentally. Includes diseases, injuries, disabilities, disorders, syndromes, etc.

Product.title: Product
Product.description: Any offered product or service. For example: a pair of shoes; a concert ticket; the rental of a car; a haircut; or an episode of a TV show streamed online.

Accommodation.title: Accommodation
Accommodation.description:
An accommodation is a place that can accommodate human beings, e.g. a hotel room, a camping pitch, or a meeting room. Many accommodations are for overnight stays, but this is not a mandatory requirement. For more specific types of accommodations not defined in schema.org, one can use additionalType with external vocabularies.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

House.title: House
House.description: A house is a building or structure that has the ability to be occupied for habitation by humans or other creatures (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House).

Joint.title: Joint
Joint.description: The anatomical location at which two or more bones make contact.

Drug.title: Drug
Drug.description: A chemical or biologic substance, used as a medical therapy, that has a physiological effect on an organism. Here the term drug is used interchangeably with the term medicine although clinical knowledge make a clear difference between them.

Taxon.title: Taxon
Taxon.description: A set of organisms asserted to represent a natural cohesive biological unit.

Game.title: Game
Game.description: The Game type represents things which are games. These are typically rule-governed recreational activities, e.g. role-playing games in which players assume the role of characters in a fictional setting.

Gene.title: Gene
Gene.description: A discrete unit of inheritance which affects one or more biological traits .

BedAndBreakfast.title: BedAndBreakfast
BedAndBreakfast.description:
Bed and breakfast.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

Service.title: Service
Service.description: A service provided by an organization, e.g. delivery service, print services, etc.

MedicalBusiness.title: MedicalBusiness
MedicalBusiness.description: A particular physical or virtual business of an organization for medical purposes. Examples of MedicalBusiness include differents business run by health professionals.

DiagnosticProcedure.title: DiagnosticProcedure
DiagnosticProcedure.description: A medical procedure intended primarily for diagnostic, as opposed to therapeutic, purposes.

MedicalDevice.title: MedicalDevice
MedicalDevice.description: Any object used in a medical capacity, such as to diagnose or treat a patient.

Person.title: Person
Person.description: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).

Vein.title: Vein
Vein.description: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries blood to the heart.

Mountain.title: Mountain
Mountain.description: A mountain, like Mount Whitney or Mount Everest.

Poster.title: Poster
Poster.description: A large, usually printed placard, bill, or announcement, often illustrated, that is posted to advertise or publicize something.
